On the other hand, Fig. 3d shows that as the nanowires become of more direct bandgap type, it is at +3% tensile strain that the sought-for NDR emerges. As the effect of applying tensile strain on the band structure is increasing the energy offset (see Fig. 3c with ΔE = 280 meV), this suggests that the indirect sub band is significantly less populated than those at 0% and −3% (e−ΔE/kBT=4.6×10−5\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
